<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7624405>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–7. Cedraderus constrictus, male morphological structures. 1) Antenna; 2) Pronotum, dorsal aspect, arrows show subapical and antebasal sulci; 3) Setation of elytral disc; 4) Mesoventrite with mesanepisterna; 5) Abdominal ventrites 1 and 2 (arrow shows suture separating the two ventrites). Aedeagus: 6) Dorsal aspect; 7) Ventral aspect. Scale bar (for Figs. 6 and 7) = 0.10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7624405/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7624407>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8–10. Cedraderus constrictus, habitus of specimens from UC James Reserve, Riverside Co., CA. Male (SBMNHENT0055168): 8) Dorsal aspect; 9) Lateral aspect. 10) Female (SBMNHENT0054966), dorsal aspect. Scale bar = 1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7624407/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

